it a whole lot better. Well David what are you going to do when you got through? First

04:16.480 --> 04:20.320
where you're going to go to college if you pass your grades and everything? Well I'd like

04:20.320 --> 04:28.000
to go to the University of Tennessee because I believe that that has one of the best education

04:28.000 --> 04:34.360
for agriculture. You may hear. You're going to be a farmer? Down at Madisonville maybe

04:34.360 --> 04:39.440
one of these days. I bet you'll be a good farmer because you like to you're always willing

04:39.440 --> 04:48.600
to mow the yard which I don't do very often. And then Diane you're like your mother you're

04:48.600 --> 04:53.680
somewhat of an artist but what is it that you like to draw? Well I like to paint horses

04:53.680 --> 04:59.720
and that's about it. Well I guess we've been talking a whole lot about how Diane paints

04:59.720 --> 05:05.920
horses and then we did mention that you went down to the studio with mummy once in a while

05:05.920 --> 05:10.000
and we might have proud of something happened about your paintings though the day what

05:10.000 --> 05:17.600
was that? Well I saw two of my paintings and I got $2.00. Oh yeah that was wonderful.

05:17.600 --> 05:21.360
I don't think a little girl ever has been so excited is when somebody paid her $10 for

05:21.360 --> 05:25.840
a painting that's. $10 for two paintings. $10 for two paintings yeah that's for a half

05:25.840 --> 05:32.600
feet. She lost a paint. Like aeol's a model isn't she? You just like to paint? No she

